Detailed Description

During a device discorvery request there were very few informations exchanged between the local device and the found remote devices. To get informations that are more exact the BtServiceVerifyRequest can be used. This kind of request lets the application programmer query one or more devices whether they support one or more particular services. It can also decide that, when a service is supported, certain attributes with their values are queried from this service and returned to the local device.

Member Function Documentation

BOOLEAN BtServiceVerifyRequest::Cancel (   )  [protected, virtual]
 

Set controller parameters and call stack to cancel operation.

The Cancel member function is responsible for setting the appropriate parameters and perform the call to the controllers function, that cancels an ongoing operation at the Bluetooth Stack. This function is pure virtual because each request is canceled in a different way and this has to be implemented by the concrete Bt...Request class.

Returns:
TRUE: The setup of the stack parameters was successfull and the Bluetooth stack accepted the requested operation.
FALSE: Either the setup of the stack parameters failed or the Bluetooth stack rejected the requested operation.

Implements BtRequest.

BOOLEAN BtServiceVerifyRequest::Execute (   )  [protected, virtual]
 

Sumbit this request to the Bluetooth Stack.

Execute instructs this request to send itself to the Bluetooth Stack for execution purposes.
In the base class of all Bluetooth Requests - BtRequest - there is an interface defined, that all requests must fullfill respectively implement. Some functions in this interface are declared pure virtual because they can not be implemented in the base classes. Execute is one of these functions.Because the execution of various requests differ very strong, the implmentation of this function is done by the various concrete request classes.

Returns:
TRUE: The setup of the stack parameters was successfull and the Bluetooth stack accepted the requested operation.
FALSE: Either the setup of the stack parameters failed or the Bluetooth stack rejected the requested operation.

Implements BtRequest.

const BtAttributeId * BtServiceVerifyRequest::GetAttributesRequested (   )  const
 

Which attriburtes should be returned.

For every verified service a BtServiceVerifyRequest can query any number up to 255 service attributes and their values. GetAttributesRequested returns these attributes that where queried from every verified serivce.

Returns:
A pointer to an array of BtAttributeId containing the attribute ids of the attributes that should be queried.

BtDeviceRelation BtServiceVerifyRequest::GetDeviceRelation (   )  const
 

Which relation should the verified devices have?

GetDeviceRelation returns the kind of relation - paired, trusted or connected - the remote devices should have to the local device. All devices in the list of devices to verify that do not match the relation condition where not verfied. A BtDeviceRelation containing the device realtion that the remote devices should have.

UINT8 BtServiceVerifyRequest::GetNumberOfServicesToVerify (   )  const
 

How many service should be verified?

A BtServiceVerifyRequest can not only verify one single service. It can verify any number of services up to 255. The function GetNumberOfServicesToVerify returns that number of services to verify.

Returns:
An UINT8 containing the number of services that should be verified.

BtRequestType BtServiceVerifyRequest::GetRequestType (   )  const [virtual]
 

Get type of this request.

The runtime type information feature is not supported by all compilers which this framework is used with. So a rudimentary type information system is implemnted by this class. Each type of request that has no subtypes (leaf class) must return an unique type identifier. GetRuestType return this type idenifier which is implemented as an enumeration type.

Returns:
A BtRequestType containing the type that describes this request.

const BtServiceVerifyResult * BtServiceVerifyRequest::GetServiceVerifyResult (  const BtDeviceAddress &  device_address  )  const
 

Return the service verify result for a specific device.

A BtServiceVerifyRequest con not only verify one single remote device. It can veriry any number of remote devices. For every remoted device queried there will be one BtServiceVerifyResult. GetServiceVerifyResult returns the service verify result for one partikular remote device identified through the passed in BtDeviceAddress. The returned pointer is valid as long as this request "lives" (exists in memory). param device_address A reference to a BtDeviceAddress containing the address of the remote device for which the servic everify result should be returned.

Returns:
A pointer to a BtServiceVerifyResult containing the service verify result for the passed in device address. If the BtServiceVerifyRequest has no result for the passed in device_address the function will return 0.

BOOLEAN BtServiceVerifyRequest::OnMessage (  const Message &  message  )  [protected, virtual]
 

Message dispatching member function.

The OnMessage member function is the first entry point in every dispatcher for the reception of messages. From there on it will be routed to the appropriate On... member function, if it should be handled by this dispatcher or passed back to the superior dispatcher.

Returns:
TRUE: The received message has be handle. No further handling for the message is needed.
FALSE: The received message is not handled by this dispatcher. Route it forward to the next dispatcher.

Implements BtLocalRequest.

void BtServiceVerifyRequest::OnServiceVerifyResultReceived (  const BtDeviceAddress &  device_address,
const WString &  device_name,
const BtServiceVerifyResult *  service_verify_result
)  [protected, virtual]
 

Service verify result received message handler member function.

The OnServiceVerifyResultReceived member function will be invoked when a BtServiceVeriryReceivedMessage is received by this request. This member function is used to enable some reactions to the receipt of the aforsaid message. The implmenetation of this member function is a dummy implementation and does nothing. If the application programmer wants to change this behaviour, he has to overload this function in a derived class. He need not to call the inherited base function, because it does nothing.

Parameters:
device_address A BtDeviceAddress containing the remote device address for which the service verify result is returned.
service_verify_result A pointer to a BtServiceVerifyResult containing the result for the device_addressy.

void BtServiceVerifyRequest::RegisterMessages (  void   )  const [protected, virtual]
 

Register the required messages for receipt.

After registering itself at an application, the request has to tell the message dispatching mechanism which messages this request is intersted in. RegisterMessage performs this task. For the BtServiceVerifyRequest the following messages are registered: BtServiceVerifyMessage, BtServiceVerifyResultMessage.

Reimplemented from UserDispatcher.
